{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Do you know how many choices you make"},{"time":2000,"text":"in a typical day?"},{"time":5000,"text":"Do you know how many choices you make"},{"time":7000,"text":"in typical week?"},{"time":9000,"text":"I recently did a survey"},{"time":11000,"text":"with over 2,000 Americans,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and the average number of choices"},{"time":15000,"text":"that the typical American reports making"},{"time":17000,"text":"is about 70 in a typical day."},{"time":20000,"text":"There was also recently a study done with CEOs"},{"time":24000,"text":"in which they followed CEOs around for a whole week."},{"time":27000,"text":"And these scientists simply documented all the various tasks"},{"time":30000,"text":"that these CEOs engaged in"},{"time":32000,"text":"and how much time they spent engaging"},{"time":34000,"text":"in making decisions related to these tasks."},{"time":36000,"text":"And they found that the average CEO"},{"time":39000,"text":"engaged in about 139 tasks in a week."},{"time":42000,"text":"Each task was made up of many, many, many sub-choices of course."},{"time":46000,"text":"50 percent of their decisions"},{"time":48000,"text":"were made in nine minutes or less."},{"time":51000,"text":"Only about 12 percent of the decisions"},{"time":54000,"text":"did they make an hour or more of their time."},{"time":58000,"text":"Think about your own choices."},{"time":60000,"text":"Do you know how many choices"},{"time":62000,"text":"make it into your nine minute category"},{"time":64000,"text":"versus your one hour category?"},{"time":66000,"text":"How well do you think you're doing"},{"time":68000,"text":"at managing those choices?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Today I want to talk"},{"time":73000,"text":"about one of the biggest modern day choosing problems that we have,"},{"time":76000,"text":"which is the choice overload problem."},{"time":78000,"text":"I want to talk about the problem"},{"time":80000,"text":"and some potential solutions."},{"time":82000,"text":"Now as I talk about this problem,"},{"time":84000,"text":"I'm going to have some questions for you"},{"time":86000,"text":"and I'm going to want to know your answers."},{"time":89000,"text":"So when I ask you a question,"},{"time":91000,"text":"since I'm blind,"},{"time":93000,"text":"only raise your hand if you want to burn off some calories."},{"time":96000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":99000,"text":"Otherwise, when I ask you a question,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and if your answer is yes,"},{"time":103000,"text":"I'd like you to clap your hands."},{"time":105000,"text":"So for my first question for you today:"},{"time":108000,"text":"Are you guys ready to hear about the choice overload problem?"},{"time":111000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":113000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"So when I was a graduate student at Stanford University,"},{"time":118000,"text":"I used to go to this very, very upscale grocery store;"},{"time":121000,"text":"at least at that time it was truly upscale."},{"time":123000,"text":"It was a store called Draeger's."},{"time":126000,"text":"Now this store, it was almost like going to an amusement park."},{"time":129000,"text":"They had 250 different kinds of mustards and vinegars"},{"time":132000,"text":"and over 500 different kinds"},{"time":134000,"text":"of fruits and vegetables"},{"time":136000,"text":"and more than two dozen different kinds of bottled water --"},{"time":139000,"text":"and this was during a time when we actually used to drink tap water."},{"time":143000,"text":"I used to love going to this store,"},{"time":146000,"text":"but on one occasion I asked myself,"},{"time":148000,"text":"well how come you never buy anything?"},{"time":150000,"text":"Here's their olive oil aisle."},{"time":152000,"text":"They had over 75 different kinds of olive oil,"},{"time":154000,"text":"including those that were in a locked case"},{"time":156000,"text":"that came from thousand-year-old olive trees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"So I one day decided to pay a visit to the manager,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and I asked the manager,"},{"time":164000,"text":"\"Is this model of offering people all this choice really working?\""},{"time":167000,"text":"And he pointed to the busloads of tourists"},{"time":169000,"text":"that would show up everyday,"},{"time":171000,"text":"with cameras ready usually."},{"time":173000,"text":"We decided to do a little experiment,"},{"time":176000,"text":"and we picked jam for our experiment."},{"time":178000,"text":"Here's their jam aisle."},{"time":180000,"text":"They had 348 different kinds of jam."},{"time":182000,"text":"We set up a little tasting booth"},{"time":184000,"text":"right near the entrance of the store."},{"time":186000,"text":"We there put out six different flavors of jam"},{"time":188000,"text":"or 24 different flavors of jam,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and we looked at two things:"},{"time":193000,"text":"First, in which case"},{"time":195000,"text":"were people more likely to stop, sample some jam?"},{"time":198000,"text":"More people stopped when there were 24, about 60 percent,"},{"time":201000,"text":"than when there were six,"},{"time":203000,"text":"about 40 percent."},{"time":205000,"text":"The next thing we looked at"},{"time":207000,"text":"is in which case were people more likely"},{"time":209000,"text":"to buy a jar of jam."},{"time":211000,"text":"Now we see the opposite effect."},{"time":213000,"text":"Of the people who stopped when there were 24,"},{"time":215000,"text":"only three percent of them actually bought a jar of jam."},{"time":218000,"text":"Of the people who stopped when there were six,"},{"time":221000,"text":"well now we saw that 30 percent of them"},{"time":223000,"text":"actually bought a jar of jam."},{"time":225000,"text":"Now if you do the math,"},{"time":227000,"text":"people were at least six times more likely to buy a jar of jam"},{"time":230000,"text":"if they encountered six"},{"time":232000,"text":"than if they encountered 24."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Now choosing not to buy a jar of jam"},{"time":236000,"text":"is probably good for us --"},{"time":238000,"text":"at least it's good for our waistlines --"},{"time":240000,"text":"but it turns out that this choice overload problem affects us"},{"time":243000,"text":"even in very consequential decisions."},{"time":246000,"text":"We choose not to choose,"},{"time":248000,"text":"even when it goes against our best self-interests."},{"time":251000,"text":"So now for the topic of today: financial savings."},{"time":254000,"text":"Now I'm going to describe to you a study I did"},{"time":258000,"text":"with Gur Huberman, Emir Kamenica, Wei Jang"},{"time":261000,"text":"where we looked at the retirement savings decisions"},{"time":265000,"text":"of nearly a million Americans"},{"time":268000,"text":"from about 650 plans"},{"time":271000,"text":"all in the U.S."},{"time":273000,"text":"And what we looked at"},{"time":275000,"text":"was whether the number of fund offerings"},{"time":277000,"text":"available in a retirement savings plan,"},{"time":279000,"text":"the 401(k) plan,"},{"time":281000,"text":"does that affect people's likelihood"},{"time":283000,"text":"to save more for tomorrow."},{"time":285000,"text":"And what we found"},{"time":287000,"text":"was that indeed there was a correlation."},{"time":290000,"text":"So in these plans, we had about 657 plans"},{"time":293000,"text":"that ranged from offering people"},{"time":295000,"text":"anywhere from two to 59 different fund offerings."},{"time":298000,"text":"And what we found was that,"},{"time":300000,"text":"the more funds offered,"},{"time":302000,"text":"indeed, there was less participation rate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"So if you look at the extremes,"},{"time":307000,"text":"those plans that offered you two funds,"},{"time":309000,"text":"participation rates were around in the mid-70s --"},{"time":312000,"text":"still not as high as we want it to be."},{"time":314000,"text":"In those plans that offered nearly 60 funds,"},{"time":317000,"text":"participation rates have now dropped"},{"time":320000,"text":"to about the 60th percentile."},{"time":323000,"text":"Now it turns out"},{"time":325000,"text":"that even if you do choose to participate"},{"time":328000,"text":"when there are more choices present,"},{"time":330000,"text":"even then, it has negative consequences."},{"time":333000,"text":"So for those people who did choose to participate,"},{"time":336000,"text":"the more choices available,"},{"time":338000,"text":"the more likely people were"},{"time":340000,"text":"to completely avoid stocks or equity funds."},{"time":343000,"text":"The more choices available,"},{"time":345000,"text":"the more likely they were"},{"time":347000,"text":"to put all their money in pure money market accounts."},{"time":349000,"text":"Now neither of these extreme decisions"},{"time":351000,"text":"are the kinds of decisions"},{"time":353000,"text":"that any of us would recommend for people"},{"time":355000,"text":"when you're considering their future financial well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"Well, over the past decade,"},{"time":360000,"text":"we have observed three main negative consequences"},{"time":363000,"text":"to offering people more and more choices."},{"time":366000,"text":"They're more likely to delay choosing --"},{"time":368000,"text":"procrastinate even when it goes against their best self-interest."},{"time":371000,"text":"They're more likely to make worse choices --"},{"time":373000,"text":"worse financial choices, medical choices."},{"time":376000,"text":"They're more likely to choose things that make them less satisfied,"},{"time":379000,"text":"even when they do objectively better."},{"time":382000,"text":"The main reason for this"},{"time":384000,"text":"is because, we might enjoy gazing at those giant walls"},{"time":388000,"text":"of mayonnaises, mustards, vinegars, jams,"},{"time":390000,"text":"but we can't actually do the math of comparing and contrasting"},{"time":393000,"text":"and actually picking from that stunning display."},{"time":397000,"text":"So what I want to propose to you today"},{"time":399000,"text":"are four simple techniques --"},{"time":402000,"text":"techniques that we have tested in one way or another"},{"time":405000,"text":"in different research venues --"},{"time":407000,"text":"that you can easily apply"},{"time":409000,"text":"in your businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"The first: Cut."},{"time":413000,"text":"You've heard it said before,"},{"time":415000,"text":"but it's never been more true than today,"},{"time":417000,"text":"that less is more."},{"time":419000,"text":"People are always upset when I say, \"Cut.\""},{"time":422000,"text":"They're always worried they're going to lose shelf space."},{"time":424000,"text":"But in fact, what we're seeing more and more"},{"time":427000,"text":"is that if you are willing to cut,"},{"time":429000,"text":"get rid of those extraneous redundant options,"},{"time":431000,"text":"well there's an increase in sales,"},{"time":433000,"text":"there's a lowering of costs,"},{"time":435000,"text":"there is an improvement of the choosing experience."},{"time":439000,"text":"When Proctor &amp; Gamble"},{"time":441000,"text":"went from 26 different kinds of Head &amp; Shoulders to 15,"},{"time":443000,"text":"they saw an increase in sales by 10 percent."},{"time":446000,"text":"When the Golden Cat Corporation"},{"time":448000,"text":"got rid of their 10 worst-selling cat litter products,"},{"time":450000,"text":"they saw an increase in profits"},{"time":452000,"text":"by 87 percent --"},{"time":454000,"text":"a function of both increase in sales"},{"time":456000,"text":"and lowering of costs."},{"time":458000,"text":"You know, the average grocery store today"},{"time":460000,"text":"offers you 45,000 products."},{"time":462000,"text":"The typical Walmart today offers you 100,000 products."},{"time":465000,"text":"But the ninth largest retailer,"},{"time":470000,"text":"the ninth biggest retailer in the world today"},{"time":472000,"text":"is Aldi,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and it offers you only 1,400 products --"},{"time":477000,"text":"one kind of canned tomato sauce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"Now in the financial savings world,"},{"time":482000,"text":"I think one of the best examples that has recently come out"},{"time":485000,"text":"on how to best manage the choice offerings"},{"time":488000,"text":"has actually been something that David Laibson was heavily involved in designing,"},{"time":491000,"text":"which was the program that they have at Harvard."},{"time":493000,"text":"Every single Harvard employee"},{"time":495000,"text":"is now automatically enrolled"},{"time":497000,"text":"in a lifecycle fund."},{"time":499000,"text":"For those people who actually want to choose,"},{"time":501000,"text":"they're given 20 funds,"},{"time":503000,"text":"not 300 or more funds."},{"time":505000,"text":"You know, often, people say,"},{"time":507000,"text":"\"I don't know how to cut."},{"time":509000,"text":"They're all important choices.\""},{"time":511000,"text":"And the first thing I do is I ask the employees,"},{"time":514000,"text":"\"Tell me how these choices are different from one another."},{"time":516000,"text":"And if your employees can't tell them apart,"},{"time":518000,"text":"neither can your consumers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"Now before we started our session this afternoon,"},{"time":524000,"text":"I had a chat with Gary."},{"time":526000,"text":"And Gary said that he would be willing"},{"time":529000,"text":"to offer people in this audience"},{"time":531000,"text":"an all-expenses-paid free vacation"},{"time":534000,"text":"to the most beautiful road in the world."},{"time":538000,"text":"Here's a description of the road."},{"time":541000,"text":"And I'd like you to read it."},{"time":543000,"text":"And now I'll give you a few seconds to read it"},{"time":545000,"text":"and then I want you to clap your hands"},{"time":547000,"text":"if you're ready to take Gary up on his offer."},{"time":549000,"text":"(Light clapping)"},{"time":551000,"text":"Okay. Anybody who's ready to take him up on his offer."},{"time":554000,"text":"Is that all?"},{"time":556000,"text":"All right, let me show you some more about this."},{"time":559000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":562000,"text":"You guys knew there was a trick, didn't you."},{"time":569000,"text":"(Honk)"},{"time":571000,"text":"Now who's ready to go on this trip."},{"time":574000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":576000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":578000,"text":"I think I might have actually heard more hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"All right."},{"time":583000,"text":"Now in fact,"},{"time":585000,"text":"you had objectively more information"},{"time":587000,"text":"the first time around than the second time around,"},{"time":589000,"text":"but I would venture to guess"},{"time":591000,"text":"that you felt that it was more real the second time around."},{"time":595000,"text":"Because the pictures made it feel"},{"time":597000,"text":"more real to you."},{"time":599000,"text":"Which brings me to the second technique"},{"time":601000,"text":"for handling the choice overload problem,"},{"time":603000,"text":"which is concretization."},{"time":605000,"text":"That in order for people to understand"},{"time":607000,"text":"the differences between the choices,"},{"time":609000,"text":"they have to be able to understand"},{"time":611000,"text":"the consequences associated with each choice,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and that the consequences need to be felt"},{"time":617000,"text":"in a vivid sort of way, in a very concrete way."},{"time":621000,"text":"Why do people spend an average of 15 to 30 percent more"},{"time":624000,"text":"when they use an ATM card or a credit card"},{"time":626000,"text":"as opposed to cash?"},{"time":628000,"text":"Because it doesn't feel like real money."},{"time":630000,"text":"And it turns out"},{"time":632000,"text":"that making it feel more concrete"},{"time":634000,"text":"can actually be a very positive tool"},{"time":636000,"text":"to use in getting people to save more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"So a study that I did with Shlomo Benartzi"},{"time":640000,"text":"and Alessandro Previtero,"},{"time":642000,"text":"we did a study with people at ING --"},{"time":646000,"text":"employees that are all working at ING --"},{"time":649000,"text":"and now these people were all in a session"},{"time":651000,"text":"where they're doing enrollment for their 401(k) plan."},{"time":654000,"text":"And during that session,"},{"time":656000,"text":"we kept the session exactly the way it used to be,"},{"time":658000,"text":"but we added one little thing."},{"time":661000,"text":"The one little thing we added"},{"time":664000,"text":"was we asked people"},{"time":666000,"text":"to just think about all the positive things that would happen in your life"},{"time":669000,"text":"if you saved more."},{"time":671000,"text":"By doing that simple thing,"},{"time":674000,"text":"there was an increase in enrollment by 20 percent"},{"time":677000,"text":"and there was an increase in the amount of people willing to save"},{"time":680000,"text":"or the amount that they were willing to put down into their savings account"},{"time":683000,"text":"by four percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"The third technique: Categorization."},{"time":688000,"text":"We can handle more categories"},{"time":691000,"text":"than we can handle choices."},{"time":693000,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":695000,"text":"here's a study we did in a magazine aisle."},{"time":697000,"text":"It turns out that in Wegmans grocery stores"},{"time":699000,"text":"up and down the northeast corridor,"},{"time":701000,"text":"the magazine aisles range anywhere"},{"time":703000,"text":"from 331 different kinds of magazines"},{"time":705000,"text":"all the way up to 664."},{"time":708000,"text":"But you know what?"},{"time":710000,"text":"If I show you 600 magazines"},{"time":712000,"text":"and I divide them up into 10 categories,"},{"time":715000,"text":"versus I show you 400 magazines"},{"time":717000,"text":"and divide them up into 20 categories,"},{"time":720000,"text":"you believe that I have given you"},{"time":722000,"text":"more choice and a better choosing experience"},{"time":724000,"text":"if I gave you the 400"},{"time":726000,"text":"than if I gave you the 600."},{"time":728000,"text":"Because the categories tell me how to tell them apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733000,"text":"Here are two different jewelry displays."},{"time":736000,"text":"One is called \"Jazz\" and the other one is called \"Swing.\""},{"time":739000,"text":"If you think the display on the left is Swing"},{"time":742000,"text":"and the display on the right is Jazz,"},{"time":745000,"text":"clap your hands."},{"time":747000,"text":"(Light Clapping)"},{"time":749000,"text":"Okay, there's some."},{"time":751000,"text":"If you think the one on the left is Jazz and the one on the right is Swing,"},{"time":753000,"text":"clap your hands."},{"time":755000,"text":"Okay, a bit more."},{"time":757000,"text":"Now it turns out you're right."},{"time":759000,"text":"The one on the left is Jazz and the one on the right is Swing,"},{"time":761000,"text":"but you know what?"},{"time":763000,"text":"This is a highly useless categorization scheme."},{"time":766000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":768000,"text":"The categories need to say something"},{"time":771000,"text":"to the chooser, not the choice-maker."},{"time":774000,"text":"And you often see that problem"},{"time":776000,"text":"when it comes down to those long lists of all these funds."},{"time":779000,"text":"Who are they actually supposed to be informing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"My fourth technique: Condition for complexity."},{"time":786000,"text":"It turns out we can actually"},{"time":788000,"text":"handle a lot more information than we think we can,"},{"time":790000,"text":"we've just got to take it a little easier."},{"time":792000,"text":"We have to gradually increase the complexity."},{"time":795000,"text":"I'm going to show you one example of what I'm talking about."},{"time":798000,"text":"Let's take a very, very complicated decision:"},{"time":800000,"text":"buying a car."},{"time":802000,"text":"Here's a German car manufacturer"},{"time":804000,"text":"that gives you the opportunity to completely custom make your car."},{"time":807000,"text":"You've got to make 60 different decisions,"},{"time":809000,"text":"completely make up your car."},{"time":811000,"text":"Now these decisions vary"},{"time":813000,"text":"in the number of choices that they offer per decision."},{"time":816000,"text":"Car colors, exterior car colors --"},{"time":818000,"text":"I've got 56 choices."},{"time":820000,"text":"Engines, gearshift -- four choices."},{"time":823000,"text":"So now what I'm going to do"},{"time":825000,"text":"is I'm going to vary the order in which these decisions appear."},{"time":828000,"text":"So half of the customers"},{"time":830000,"text":"are going to go from high choice, 56 car colors,"},{"time":832000,"text":"to low choice, four gearshifts."},{"time":835000,"text":"The other half of the customers"},{"time":837000,"text":"are going to go from low choice, four gearshifts,"},{"time":839000,"text":"to 56 car colors, high choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"What am I going to look at?"},{"time":844000,"text":"How engaged you are."},{"time":846000,"text":"If you keep hitting the default button per decision,"},{"time":849000,"text":"that means you're getting overwhelmed,"},{"time":851000,"text":"that means I'm losing you."},{"time":853000,"text":"What you find"},{"time":855000,"text":"is the people who go from high choice to low choice,"},{"time":857000,"text":"they're hitting that default button over and over and over again."},{"time":860000,"text":"We're losing them."},{"time":862000,"text":"They go from low choice to high choice,"},{"time":864000,"text":"they're hanging in there."},{"time":866000,"text":"It's the same information. It's the same number of choices."},{"time":869000,"text":"The only thing that I have done"},{"time":871000,"text":"is I have varied the order"},{"time":873000,"text":"in which that information is presented."},{"time":875000,"text":"If I start you off easy,"},{"time":877000,"text":"I learn how to choose."},{"time":879000,"text":"Even though choosing gearshift"},{"time":882000,"text":"doesn't tell me anything about my preferences for interior decor,"},{"time":885000,"text":"it still prepares me for how to choose."},{"time":888000,"text":"It also gets me excited about this big product that I'm putting together,"},{"time":891000,"text":"so I'm more willing to be motivated"},{"time":893000,"text":"to be engaged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"So let me recap."},{"time":897000,"text":"I have talked about four techniques"},{"time":900000,"text":"for mitigating the problem of choice overload --"},{"time":903000,"text":"cut -- get rid of the extraneous alternatives;"},{"time":906000,"text":"concretize -- make it real;"},{"time":909000,"text":"categorize -- we can handle more categories, less choices;"},{"time":913000,"text":"condition for complexity."},{"time":916000,"text":"All of these techniques that I'm describing to you today"},{"time":919000,"text":"are designed to help you manage your choices --"},{"time":922000,"text":"better for you, you can use them on yourself,"},{"time":925000,"text":"better for the people that you are serving."},{"time":927000,"text":"Because I believe that the key"},{"time":929000,"text":"to getting the most from choice"},{"time":931000,"text":"is to be choosy about choosing."},{"time":934000,"text":"And the more we're able to be choosy about choosing"},{"time":936000,"text":"the better we will be able"},{"time":938000,"text":"to practice the art of choosing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}